   <text>
      <body>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="50" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="1">
            <l n="1">Strange fits of passion I have known:</l>
            <l n="2">And I will dare to tell,</l>
            <l n="3">But in the Lover’s ear alone,</l>
            <l n="4">What once to me befel.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="2">
            <l n="5">When she I loved, was strong and gay</l>
            <l n="6">And like a rose in June,</l>
            <l n="7">I to her cottage bent my way,</l>
            <l n="8">Beneath the evening Moon.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="3">
            <l n="9">Upon the Moon I fixed my eye,</l>
            <l n="10">All over the wide lea:</l>
            <l n="11">My Horse trudged on—and we drew nigh</l>
            <l n="12">Those paths so dear to me.</l>
         </lg>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="51" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="4">
            <l n="13">And now we reached the orchard plot;</l>
            <l n="14">And, as we climbed the hill,</l>
            <l n="15">Towards the roof of Lucy’s cot</l>
            <l n="16">The Moon descended still.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="5">
            <l n="17">In one of those sweet dreams I slept,</l>
            <l n="18">Kind Nature’s gentlest boon!</l>
            <l n="19">And, all the while, my eyes I kept</l>
            <l n="20">On the descending Moon.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="6">
            <l n="21">My Horse moved on; hoof after hoof</l>
            <l n="22">
               <del hand="RS" resp="RS" type="crossout">He raised, and
                                        never stopped</del>
               <add hand="RS" place="aboveline" resp="RS"> The moon was in the sky</add>:</l>
            <l n="23">When down behind the cottage roof</l>
            <l n="24">
               <del hand="RS" resp="RS" type="crossout">At once the Planet
                                        dropped</del>.<add hand="RS" place="aboveline" resp="RS">
                                        She vanished instantly.</add>
            </l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="7">
            <l n="25">What fond and wayward thoughts will slide</l>
            <l n="26">Into a Lover’s head—</l>
            <l n="27">“O mercy!” to myself I cried,</l>
            <l n="28">“If Lucy should be dead!”</l>
         </lg>
      </body>
